s.text: The NYT runs a front-page feature by sports long-form legend Robert Lipsyte on the first major league baseball player to come out extensively to the press (in a previous article in the Miami Herald ), a retired utility player named Billy Bean who played with the Tigers, Dodgers and Padres.
